content.description: Start at the right side of the wall. Climb up the face past two bolts and then trend slightly left and up past two more bolts to a double bolt anchor

A long traverse across the entire Satellite Wall from right to left. Start by climbing to the first bolt on Vicious. Move up to the next horizontal and traverse left to the first bolt on Perfect Day. Climb Perfect Day to the forth bolt. Move up to the next horizontal and traverse left. Follow the bolt line left past four more bolts to a ring anchor.
content.location: Start on the right side of Satellite Wall

content.description: Start 15 to the left of Vicious. Climb up and left past four bolts. The crux is between bolts 2-3. Finish at a ring anchor up and left of the forth bolt.

Start 15 uphill and left of Perfect Day. Climb direct up the face past two bolts and clip the forth bolt on Perfect Day. Finish at the same anchors as Perfect Day. Syd Howard did a line in this area on gear prior to the bolts. Maybe not the same?
Start at the right side of the Satellite Wall. Climb up the face just left of the the roofs. When above the roof traverse right out to the arete. Finish up to the trees above.
content.location: Right side of the Satellite Wall

pathTokens: New Durham Area  (Longstack, Devil's Den, Rines Hill, etc.)

content.description: This is a wild little wall. It's gently overhanging and  has rock reminiscent of the Gunks. It is located just around the corner left of the Right End. This wall has been climbed on trad gear,soloed, but it is quite brittle and most will choose to clip the bolts. The bolts were added to make it a "workout wall". A great place to go run laps and get a good pump on.
